    <statement><div><p>Which of the following numbers are irrational? <alert>Exactly three</alert> of the numbers are irrational. Selecting more or fewer will result in an incorrect answer.</p>
<p/><ol marker="(1)">
<li><m>3 \sqrt{7}</m></li>
<li><m>-4</m></li>
<li><m>\sqrt{5}</m></li>
<li><m>\frac{4}{7}</m></li>
<li><m>2^{\frac{3}{2}}</m></li>
<li><m>7</m></li>
</ol> </div></statement>
    <solution><div><p><alert>Worked Solution</alert></p>
<p>An <alert>irrational number</alert> is a number that cannot be written in the form <m>\displaystyle \frac{p}{q} </m>, where <m> p </m> and <m> q </m> are integers and <m> q \neq 0 </m>.</p>
<p>To decide whether a number is rational or irrational, use the following rules:</p>
<ul>
<li><alert>Square roots:</alert> If the number inside the square root is a <em>perfect square</em>, the result is rational. If it is <em>not</em> a perfect square, the result is irrational.</li>
<li><alert>Special numbers:</alert> The numbers <m> \pi </m> and <m> e </m> are irrational.</li>
<li><alert>Decimals:</alert>
<ul>
<li>Decimals that <em>terminate</em> or <em>repeat</em> are rational.</li>
<li>Decimals that <em>do not terminate and do not repeat</em> are irrational.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Applying these rules to the given list, the irrational numbers are:</p>
<p><me>\displaystyle {\sqrt{5}},\; {2^{\frac{3}{2}}},\; {3 \sqrt{7}} </me></p>
<p><em>If you selected any other numbers, check which rule above applies to them and revise your choice.</em></p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>(1), (3), (5)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>